definition: The verbatim location ID from the originating source dataset assigned by the monitoring program.
noteAndConventions: verbatimLocationID is the unique identifiers from the source datasets all converted to data type string. Maintaining the link to location and event identifiers from the source datasets.

definition: The type of site selection used according to the program.
NAdefinition: Site selection not known or reported by the program.

definition: The name of the water body in which the location occurs.
NAdefinition: Water body name not reported in the original dataset.

definition: The verbatim event ID from the originating source dataset assigned by the program.
NAdefinition: Event ID was not included or reported in the source dataset.
noteAndConventions: verbatimEventID are the unique identifiers from the source datasets all convert to data type string. By maintaining the link to location and event identifiers from the source datasets, the data user can trace information back to the source.

definition: The calendar date of the event from the source data.
NAdefinition: Source data from AREMP do not contain month or day, so no there is no eventDate for those entries.

definition: The description of flow for the reach (flow, partial flow or dry).
NAdefinition: Description of the flow was not included or reported in the source dataset.
noteAndConventions:
fieldNotes is a field with data type string for this implementation of the data exchange standard fieldNotes is filled in with the streamflow at the time of the sampling event. Some datasets share flow as percent dry an integer, while others share streamflow as a string. For the integrated dataset, transform all stream flows string categorized as "No Flow (Dry)", "Flow (Whole Reach)", "Other". For programs reporting streamflow as percent dry, we transformed the data such that: 
•	0 = Flow (Whole Reach)  
•	100 = No Flow (Dry) 
•	Other = All other values
We transformed the data in inverse for programs that report the percent of the reach with the flow.

definition: A unique identifier assigned to the originating source data's program.
noteAndConventions: datasetID is a unique identifiers integer generated when the datasets are combined into the single dataset

definition: A bibliographic reference for the resource as a statement indicating how this record should be cited (attributed) when used.
NAdefinition: There is no formal citation for this dataset.

definition: A URL identifier for the collection or dataset from which the record was derived. The source location for the originating source data or program website.
NAdefinition: No URL is available to access the dataset directly.

definition: The name of the originating data set from which the record was derived.
NAdefinition: There is no singular name assigned to the source dataset
examples: EPA NARS 2018 Rivers and Streams dataset

definition: The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.
A URL identifier for the metadata for the originating source dataset or note how to access metadata.
URL identifier for access to the code used to pre-process (download, standardize and tidy) the data sets before integration into the destination dataset.
NAdefinition: Pre-processing code was not used for this dataset.

definition: The acronym of the name assigned by the Institution (project leader or principal investigator) to the project, from which the source data originates from.
The name assigned by the Institution (project leader or principal investigator) to the project, from which the source data originates from.
examples: USFS PacFish/InFish Biological Opinion Monitoring Program

definition: A unique numeric identifier assigned to the originating source data's program.
Unique global identifier assigned to the location where the event occurred.
noteAndConventions: locationID is a unique identifiers integer generated when the datasets are combined into a single dataset

definition: The geographic latitude (WGS84) of the geographic center of a location.
noteAndConventions: All latitude and longitudes need to be in the coordinate reference system is World Geodetic System 1984 (WGS84), not projected.

definition: The geographic longitude (WGS84) of the geographic center of a location.
noteAndConventions: All latitude and longitudes need to be in the coordinate reference system is World Geodetic System 1984 (WGS84), not projected.

definition: The location along the reach where geographic coordinates were obtained.
Unique global identifier assigned to the location where the event occurred.
Global unique identifier assigned to an Event (something that occurs at a place and time, such as a survey or measurement).
noteAndConventions: eventID is a unique identifiers integer generated when the datasets are combined into a single dataset

definition: The name of, reference to, or description of the stream survey method or protocol used during an Event.
NAdefinition: Sampling Protocol was not included or reported in the source dataset.

definition: Beaver impact on the flow of the reach.
NAdefinition: Beaver impacts were not reported in the source data.
noteAndConventions: NA = Beaver impacts were not reported in the source data, Yes = Beaver have changed the flow in the reach, No = Beaver have not changed the flow of the reach

definition: The four-digit year in which the event occurred.
Global unique identifier assigned to an Event (something that occurs at a place and time, such as a survey or measurement).
Unique identifier assigned to the measurementValue.
noteAndConventions: measurementID is a unique identifier integer generated when the datasets are combined into the single datasets.

definition: The variable, name or type of measurement for which the value is reported in measurementValue. Definitions are in the MetricControlledVocabulary.
Unique identifier assigned to the measurementType.
The value of the measurementType attribute measured in units given in the measurementType attribute definition and in the MetricControlledVocabulary.
